<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,283,470]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,426,283,309]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Remarks</emphasis>
: Studies on Brazilian mussids have pointed out important reproductive trends within the family. The endemic genus 
<taxonomicName box="[789,930,324,349]" class="Anthozoa" family="Mussidae" genus="Mussismilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[789,930,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Mussismilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
composed by colonial reef building corals 
<emphasis box="[389,526,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
(
<taxonomicName box="[398,526,364,389]" class="Anthozoa" family="Mussidae" genus="Mussismilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="hispida">M. hispida</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[542,902,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicName box="[542,659,364,389]" class="Anthozoa" family="Mussidae" genus="Mussismilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="harttii">M. harttii</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[726,902,364,389]" class="Anthozoa" family="Mussidae" genus="Mussismilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="braziliensis">M. braziliensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) are entirely represented by broadcast spawning species while the solitary 
<taxonomicName box="[735,833,404,429]" class="Anthozoa" family="Mussidae" genus="Scolymia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="wellsi">
<emphasis box="[735,833,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">S. wellsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
broods the planulae (Neves 
<number box="[1163,1225,404,430]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="2002.0">2002</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pires" pageId="6" pageNumber="54" refString="Pires, D. O., Castro, C. B., Ratto C. C. (1999) Reef coral reproduction in the Abrolhos Reef Complex, Brazil: The endemic genus Mussismilia. Marine Biology, 135 (3), 463 - 471." type="journal article" year="1999">
Pires 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[302,365,444,470]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
